---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Docs - Paunix Guard">
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Docs"
    title="Arm, step away, return with your PIN."
    lead="These docs cover the current desktop build. Phone pairing and cloud relay are future companion features, not requirements for protection."
  />

  <section class="page-shell section feature-grid">
    <article>
      <h3>First run</h3>
      <p>Install Paunix Guard, create a PIN in the setup wizard, choose the starter protection settings, and continue into the main app.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Arming</h3>
      <p>Click Start Guard when the laptop is positioned and connected as expected. A short grace period prevents immediate false alarms from setup movement.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Disarming</h3>
      <p>Enter your PIN on the guard screen or alarm window. Two wrong PIN attempts trigger the alarm as a brute-force protection measure.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Updates</h3>
      <p>Velopack-installed builds can check for updates while idle. If the guard is armed, disarm before installing an update.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
